# Implementation Plan - SOP & Work Order Integration

This plan details the steps to integrate Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) directly into the Work Order workflow for engineers.

## Proposed Changes

### [Work Order Module]

#### [MODIFY] [WorkOrderDetailsModal.tsx](file:///c:/Users/princ/3D%20Objects/HaulageTracker/src/app/dashboard/maintain/work-orders/components/WorkOrderDetailsModal.tsx)
- **New State**: Add `showSOPChecklist` and `selectedSOP` states.
- **SOP Lookup**: When the modal opens, if an asset is linked, search the local SOPs for a matching `asset_type`.
- **"Execute SOP Checklist" Button**:
    - Add a button in the **Asset** detail row of the View Mode.
    - Visibility: Only show when `workOrder.status === 'in_progress'`.
    - Styling: Use a distinct maintenance color (emerald or blue) with a `ClipboardCheck` icon.
- **SOP Modal Integration**:
    - Render the [SOPModal](file:///c:/Users/princ/3D%20Objects/HaulageTracker/src/app/dashboard/maintain/knowledge-base/components/SOPModal.tsx#50-414) as a child component.
    - Configure it for `isEngineer` (checklist) mode.
    - Pass the current `workOrder.id` to the [SOPModal](file:///c:/Users/princ/3D%20Objects/HaulageTracker/src/app/dashboard/maintain/knowledge-base/components/SOPModal.tsx#50-414) props.

## User Flow
1. Engineer opens an **Assigned** Work Order.
2. Engineer clicks **"Start Work"**.
3. Once the status is **"In Progress"**, the **"Execute SOP Checklist"** button becomes active.
4. Engineer clicks the button to open the procedure.
5. Engineer ticks off steps as they work.
6. Engineer clicks **"Submit Execution"** to save the record permanently.
7. Engineer records final diesel/meter readings and closes the Work Order.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- N/A (Manual Verification in Browser)

### Manual Verification
1. Log in as an **Engineer**.
2. Open a Work Order and click **"Start Work"**.
3. Verify that the **"Execute SOP Checklist"** button appears.
4. Click the button and verify the correct SOP opens for that asset type.
5. Tick multiple steps and click **"Submit Execution"**.
6. Switch to an **Admin** account and verify the execution record appears in the database/logs.
